<package >
  <metadata>
    <id>soothsayer</id>
    <version>$version$</version>
    <title>soothsayer</title>
    <authors>PayByPhone, Phillip Wong</authors>
    <owners>PayByPhone, Phillip Wong</owners>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/paybyphone/soothsayer</projectUrl>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>Command-line migration tool for Oracle, using SQL*Plus scripts.</description>
    <releaseNotes>
	  v1.20 (Mulberry Malamute)
	    * Scripts that are run against a target database are now stored in an `appliedscripts` table.
	    * When performing a `down` migration, the `--usestored` switch may be used to tell soothsayer to use the stored scripts instead of those in the database script `/down` folder.
	    * soothsayer is now built with the official Oracle Managed Drivers NuGet package.
	    * Added support for targetting multiple environments in the command line arguments, so that scripts matching any of the supplied environments will be picked up and run against the target database.
    </releaseNotes>
    <copyright>Copyright PayByPhone 2015-2016</copyright>
    <tags>oracle database migrations scripts</tags>
  </metadata>
